<TITLE>November 1996:  Alternatives in Philanthropy</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="/crc/images/bg.gif">
<a href="/crc/images/sidebar.map"><img src="/crc/images/sidebar.gif" alt="Navigation Bar" border="O" align="left" ISMAP></a>
<blockquote>
<center>
<img src="/crc/images/hdr-ap.gif"><br>
</center>
<I>November 1996</I><BR>
<h2>Legal Services for the Poor</h2>
<hr>
<h3>Is Federal Support Necessary?</h3>
<FONT  SIZE=+1>By David Wilkinson</FONT></B><BR>
<p>

<TABLE CELLPADDING=15 CELLSPACING=10>
<tr><td width=4000 valign="left">
<UL>
<LI><a href="#1">The House of Representatives's Aborted Plan</a><br>
<LI><a href="#2">States Move To Fill The Gap</a><br>
<LI><a href="#3">A Conspiracy of Silence</a><br>
<LI><a href="#4">The LSC's Questionable Data</a><br>
<LI><a href="#5">Subgrantees' Non-LSC Funding</a><BR>
<LI><a href="#6">Total Non-LSC Funding</a><BR>
<LI><a href="#7">The Future of Legal Services for the Poor</a><br>
<LI><a href="#Table I">Tables I,</a> <a href="#Table II">II,</a> <a href="#Table III">III</a>
<LI><a href="#8">Pro Bono Legal Services for the Poor"</a>
</UL>
</td>
<td>
<BR>
<FONT  SIZE=-1><P>
<FONT  SIZE=+1>Terrence Scanlon, Publisher</FONT>
