<HTML>
<Title>Empower America - Reality Check</Title>
<Body BGCOLOR="FFFFFF">
<p>
<img src="/empower/easmall.gif">
<p>
<blockquote>
<center><H2>The Empower America Reality Check</H2>
<i>A regular tip sheet faxed free of charge to news and talk radio coast-to-coast</i><br>
<H3>A MESSAGE TO HOLLYWOOD: <i>Sleaze Doesnt Sell</i></H3></center>
<p>
<ul>
<li>In the absence of strong families, good schools and faithful churches and 
by the power of their own appeal, movies have become an increasingly 
dominant force on our social landscape.
<li>The real and most important power of film is its capacity to alter moral 
sensibilities, and to mold dispositions, outlooks, and habits of the mind 
and heart. The consistent bombardment of gratuitous violence, sexual 
innuendo, profanity, and degradation from popular movies eventually 
shapes, alters, and colors our sensibility.
<li>Despite the significant number of films in the category of <i>Showgirls, 
Striptease, Pulp Fiction</i>, and <i>Natural Born Killers</i> we have seen a 
resurgence in movies that promote traditional moral values such as: <br>
<center>Honor -- <i>Braveheart</i><br>
Courage -- <i>Apollo 13</i><br>
Patriotism -- <i>Independence Day</i><br>
Faithfulness -- <i>Forest Gump</i><br>
Perseverance -- <i>Babe</i><p></center>

<li>In fact, seven of the ten top-grossing movies of 1995 had ratings of G, 
PG, or PG-13 and all of the ten top-grossing movies of all-time had 
ratings of G, PG or PG-13 and are considered family oriented.
<p>
<b>THE YEAR'S TOP MOVIES
</b>
<br>
The year's highest-grossing movies at US and Canadian theatres, as compiled by Exhibitor Relations Co. Inc., and the rating for each.  Dollar amounts are in the millions.
<pre>
<hr>
Rank  Title                                 Gross           Rating
<hr>
 1.   Batman Forever                        $184            PG-13
 2.   Apollo 13                             $172            PG
 3.   Pocahontas                            $141.4          G
 4.   Toy Story                             $115.7          G
 5.   Ace Ventura: When Nature Calls        $102.9          PG-13
 6.   Casper                                $100.3          PG
 7.   Die Hard With A Vengence              $100            R
 8.   Crimson Tide                          $91.4           R
 9.   Waterworld                            $88.2           PG-13
 10.  Seven                                 $87             R
<hr>
</pre>
<p>
<b>ALL-TIME TOPS</b>
<br>
The top-grossing films of all time.  Dollar amounts are in the millions.
<pre>
<hr>
Rank  Title                        Gross      Rating   Opened
<hr>
 1.   ET                           399.8      PG       June 1982
 2.   Jurassic Park                356.8      PG-13    June 1993
 3.   Forrest Gump                 329.7      PG-13    July 1994
 4.   Star Wars                    322.7      PG       May 1977
 5.   The Lion King                312.9      G        June 1994
 6.   Home Alone                   285        PG       Nov 1990
 7.   Return of the Jedi           263.7      PG       May 1983
 8.   Jaws                         260        PG       June 1975
 9.   Batman                       251.2      PG-13    June 1989
 10.  Raiders of the Lost Ark      242.4      PG       June 1981
<hr>
*This information obtained from an <a href="/empower/new/clean-95.htm">article by Joyce Price</a>
 <i>The Washington Times</i>
</pre>
<p> 
<li>These numbers indicate progress can and has been made through moral 
suasion and market forces, not government intervention. Empower 
America intends to keep making the case that civilization needs cultural 
guardrails and certain reliable standards of right and wrong that may not 
be enforceable in law but must be enforceable through conscience and 
consensus.
</ul>
<p>
<i>Empower America</i>, led by Jack Kemp, William Bennett, Lamar 
Alexander, Jeane Kirkpatrick, and Vin Weber is Americas leading grass-
roots conservative advocacy organization.
<p>
<b>To talk to a policy expert on this and other issues contact:</b><br>
David Dardis at Empower America<br>
1776 I Street, N.W. #890<br>
Washington D.C 20006<br>
202/452-8200<br>
fax: 202/833-0388<p>

<b>For Your Listeners:</b><br>

To join Empower America, call our toll free membership hotline, 1 (800) 332-2000.

<p><br>
<center>
| <a href="/empower/">Home</a> |</center>
<p><br>
</blockquote>
