<P>

12/17/96<br>
The Courts absolutely must be given the message that they exist to carry out the laws of the land, in addition to throwing out those that violate the Constitutional rights of the people. The Courts DO NOT have the right to legislate through their judicial process. The role of Congress must be, collectively, individually, and through its Judiciary Committees, to ensure that all candidates for appointment are well grounded in the historical, Christian religious basis for their role. The basic foundations of right and wrong derive from our Founding Fathers' actions and words during the writing and adoption of the Declaration of Independence, and the Constitution. Members of Congress must recognize this, affirm it, and demonstrate it during their formal proceedings such as in the Senate's advise and consent function, or be candidates for ousting at the next election. American citizens must recognize their moral responsibility in this process, and not be duped by the liberal establishment including the teachers' unions, if the decaying process of this Republic is to be stopped!! The new Congress must be bold, and LEADERS must step forward with personal conviction!<br> 
<I>Bill</I>
