The American public is the only hope for reining in the federal court Frankenstein monster! Congress is basically useless in this day and age. The American people will, eventually, simply tell the courts to "go to hell" in the same manner as they did the "Dred-Scott" courts back in the 1800s. If the people do this via Congress, it will require a massive overthrow of both the Democrats and Republicans who have created the judicial beast through apathy and politics. We are currently being ruled by a 54 black-robed oligarchy that ignores traditional U.S. (not-multicultural) traditions and institutions. If not altered, the country is going to collapse in the not-so-distant future.<br> 
