<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE> A Message From Tom Kelly, President</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
<center>
<img src="/savers/images/griffwh.gif" alt=""><br>
<img src="/savers/images/logoltwh.gif" alt="SAVERS & INVESTORS LEAGUE"><br>
</center>
<hr>
<p>
Welcome.<BR>
<P>
The Savers &amp; Investors League has developed and installed this Web site to help individuals across the country better understand a most serious problem: the irrational taxation of saving and investing.
<P>
Savers and investors do not fare well when it comes to tax legislation.  Not only is the existing income tax severely and improperly biased against saving and investing, savers and investors, as a group, have little political muscle within Congress or Administrations.  This must change.
<P>
There are many excellent organizations and associations that support the needs and desires of savers and investors, such as mutual fund, banking, stock broker, and insurance associations.  However, when priorities are paramount, as is so evident when legislation is formulated, the vital business interests of trade associations, not savers and investors, predominate. 
<P>
Savers and investors are found in all walks of life, in every geographic location, and their interests are fully compatible with the interests of labor; one can't exist and prosper without the other.  It is increasingly being realized that the tax-efficient accumulation of capital is vital to the interests of <EM>all</EM> segments of our society, whether it be labor, capital, or government.  The government produces nothing on its own; its basic sustenance  is from the taxation of capital and labor. When government needlessly and improperly impedes the economic growth of capital, it increasingly impedes the economic growth of labor.  Concurrently, the government  curtails its own tax base.
<P>
The Savers &amp; Investors League is aggressively fighting to remove the government's existing improper and self-defeating tax bias against saving and investing.  The League's activities have political strength directly related to its grass-roots membership within each Congressional District.  Members of Congress do pay attention to the expressed interests of their constituents.  You can easily recognize that each vote counts.  Thus, the League urges and warrants your enthusiastic and active support.  Only by the collective, focused, and sustained action of voter/taxpayers will corrective legislation become law.  The sound taxation of saving and investing will increase jobs and increase our peoples' standard of living.
<P>
 We invite you to explore our Web site.  Read about the actual legislation pending in Congress that could dramatically change the way our Nation taxes your savings and investments.  Review related articles and research reports that support the need for sound, concise tax laws.  Join us as our newest member by filling out and sending in our <A HREF="/savers/member.html">Membership Form</A>. 

We hope the information provided will interest you and prompt you to want to know more and do more about this vital subject.  We stand ready to respond to your enquiries and comments.
<P>
Sincerely,<BR>
<P>
W. Thomas Kelly<BR>
President<BR>
<p>
<hr>
[<a href="/savers/welcome.html">Home</a>]
</BODY>
</HTML>
