<html><head>
<title>Selected Legislation - Listed by Bill #</title>
</head>
<body><body bgcolor="#FFFFFF" link="#2F4F2F" vlink="#3232CD">
<center><img src ="/savers/images/griffgrn.gif"><br>
<img src="images/logoltwh.gif"><br>
<hr>
<font size=5><b>Selected Congressional Legislation</b></font><br>
<font size=4><b>Listed by Bill Number</b></font>
</center>
<hr>
<p>
<font size=3><b><i>House Bills</i></b></font>
<p>
<ul>
<li><a href="/savers/legislation/hr56.html">H.R. 56</a> Capital Formation and Job Creation Act of 1995 (Mr. 
Archer)
<br>
<li><a href="/savers/legislation/hr328.html">H.R. 328</a> or (<a 
href="/savers/legislation/iiasumm.html">Summary</a>) The Individual 
Investment Account Act (<a href ="/savers/library/mccrery.html">Mr. McCrery</a>)
<br>
<li><a href="/savers/legislation/hr333.html">H.R. 333</a> To allow deductions for capital gains for middle
income taxpayers. (Mr. Neal of MA)
<br>
<li><a href="/savers/legislation/hr334.html">H.R. 334</a> To encourage savings by increasing the amount of 
deductible contributions which may be made to an IRA. (Mr. Neal of MA)
<br>
<li><a href="/savers/legislation/hr538.html">H.R. 538</a> To reduce the lowest individual tax rate to 12.5%, and
for other purposes. (Mr. Owens)
<br>
<li><a href="/savers/legislation/hr593.html">H.R. 593</a> To increase  the dollar limit on one-time exclusion of gain
from the sale of a principal residence by those 55 years or older, to increase the amount of unified
estate and gift tax credits, and to reduce the tax on capital gains. 
(Mr.Rohrabacher) <br>
<li><a href="/savers/legislation/hr682.html">H.R. 682</a> To encourage savings and investments through 
IRA's, etc. (Mr. Thomas of CA)
<br>
<li><a href="/savers/legislation/hr708.html">H.R. 708</a> To allow homemakers to get a full IRA deduction. 
(Mrs. Johnson of CT)
<br>
<li><a href="/savers/legislation/hr1039.html">H.R. 1039</a> To repeal estate and gift taxes and the tax on 
generation-skipping transfers. (Mr. Crane)
<br>
